### ImportName {#a725bbf09993e1c1df0b25bc925d0aa86}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="std::string llvm::object::COFFShortExport::ImportName">
Creates an import library entry that imports from a DLL export with a different name.

This is the name of the DLL export that should be referenced when linking against this import library entry. In a .def file, this is &quot;baz&quot; in &quot;EXPORTS\\nfoo = bar == baz&quot;.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/object/coffimportfile-h/#l00105">105</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/object/coffimportfile-h">COFFImportFile.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### Name {#a00b2b7630ab895b6eeb27dd2081b4429}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="std::string llvm::object::COFFShortExport::Name">
The name of the export as specified in the .def file or on the command line, i.e.

&quot;foo&quot; in &quot;/EXPORT:foo&quot;, and &quot;bar&quot; in &quot;/EXPORT:foo=bar&quot;. This may lack mangling, such as underscore prefixing and stdcall suffixing.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/object/coffimportfile-h/#l00091">91</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/object/coffimportfile-h">COFFImportFile.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="std::string llvm::object::COFFShortExport::SymbolName">
The real, mangled symbol name from the object file.

Given &quot;/export:foo=bar&quot;, this could be &quot;&#95;bar@8&quot; if bar is stdcall.
